               <p>JOHN ROBERTS. I am a <rs id="t18280221-126-viclabel667" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-126-victim820 t18280221-126-viclabel667"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-126-crimeloc668">Tottenham-place</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-126-crimeloc668" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-place"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-126-crimeloc668" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-126-off665 t18280221-126-crimeloc668"></join>. On the 4th of February, about half-past nine o'clock, I went into my parlour, and soon after I heard a noise in my shop; I went into the shop immediately, shut the shop door, and locked it; I turned towards the counter, and saw the prisoner's head just above the counter; he got up, and came part of the way round the counter: I secured him - my till was taken out, but had not been carried away; I had shut it too just before I went into the parlour.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15.</p>
